title.description: It is proposed to introduce daily trains between Chennai and New Delhi in both directions simultaneously, departing at each station at 6.00PM. If the travel time is 36 hours, what is the minimum number of rakes (train sets) required to run the service?

ansDescription.text:
Explanation:

Let the speed of the train be x km/hr.

Relative speed = (x + 5) km/hr = 5 (x+ 5)/ 18 m/sec. (Since the

directions of their motion is opposite)

Distance covered in passing the man = 100m.

100/ (5(x+5)/18) = 9

45 (x+ 5) = 1800

x + 5 = 40

x = 35.

Speed of the train = 35 km/hr.

Answer (4)
